@prefix : <https://w3id.org/geko/#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@base <https://w3id.org/geko/#> .

<https://w3id.org/geko/#> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
                           owl:versionIRI <https://w3id.org/geko/v2/#> ;
                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0009-0003-0559-0409> ;
                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "GEkO Ontology describes the phenomenon of ekphrasis along with technical implementation of image-text relations using annotations."@en ;
                           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "GEkO Ontology v2" ;
                           owl:priorVersion <https://w3id.org/geko/v1/#> ;
                           owl:versionInfo "2.0.0" ;
                           <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#changeNote> "**Version 2 Changelog** Introduction of four aspects: - hasForm ObjectProperty deprecated; NotionalEkphrasis and MimeticEkphrasis classes become subClassOf Ekphrasis - Aligment of Ekphrasis with CIDOC-CRM instantiated as subClassOf E33_Linguistic_Object - Transition to SKOS Concept to identify the ekphrastic modelities (denotation, dynamization, integration), prior modeled as classes - Definition of an ObjectProperty hasAuthor for signaling the author of Ekphrasis, more specifical than dct:creator"@en .

